Text:
Reason for visit (RFV): Broken glasses.
Last eye examination (LEE): 1.5 years ago.
Glasses: distance (DV) good  and  near vision (NV) good.
Vision: distance vision (DV) with glasses not as good as contact lenses (CL. 
Contact lens (CL) wearer with prescription (Rx) of RE: -7.00, LE: -6.50. Contact lenses are Total Dailies with last aftercare (A/C) appointment 2 weeks ago. 
General health (GH): good health, no diabetes, high blood pressure.
Medications (Meds)/ Allergies: None 
Ocular History (OH): No eye strain, no redness, no diplopia, no lazy eye, no patching young, no flashes. Patient does have floaters, first noticed 5 year ago, but they have not changed recently. 3 years ago had laser treatment for lattice degeneration (HES), no problems since then. 
Family general health (FGH): no one in the family has diabetes, high blood pressure, or heart problems.
Family ocular history (FOH): no glaucoma( glauc), AMD or cataracts.
Screen use (VDU): Laptop use 5 to 6 hours (hrs) daily, mobile phone use 3 hours per day. 
Hobbies: gym, walking. 
Occupation: student. 
Drive: Yes with specs.
Smokes: No.
